# MindRei Cursor Rules

## Icon Rules - CRITICAL
- ONLY use `lucide-react` for icons
- NEVER use emojis, unicode symbols, HTML entities, or other icon libraries
- Example: `import { Mic, Brain } from "lucide-react"`

## Code Style
- TypeScript for ALL files
- Do NOT add comments unless explicitly requested
- Do NOT delete existing comments unless explicitly requested
- Use custom Pixel* components (PixelCard, PixelButton, PixelBadge, PixelInput)

## Design Tokens
Reference `src/lib/design-tokens.ts` for:
- Colors (teal primary, amber accent, warm backgrounds)
- Typography (Space Grotesk for headings, Noto Sans for body)
- Spacing, radius, shadows, animations

## CSS Classes (from globals.css)
- `.fantasy-card` - Glass morphism cards with hover effects
- `.liquid-glass` - Strong glass effect
- `.glass-panel` - Subtle glass effect
- `.teal-glow` / `.orange-glow` - Glow effects
- `.calm-transition` - Smooth 600ms transitions
- `.calm-fade-in` / `.calm-scale-in` - Entry animations
- `.bento-grid` / `.bento-item` - Grid layouts
- `.shimmer` - Loading shimmer effect

## SEO Requirements
Every page MUST have:
- Proper `<title>` via Next.js metadata
- Meta description (150-160 chars)
- Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url)
- Twitter Card tags (twitter:card, twitter:title, twitter:description)
- Semantic HTML structure (header, main, section, article, footer)
- JSON-LD structured data for rich snippets

## Performance Requirements
- Use Next.js `<Image>` component for all images
- Implement lazy loading for below-fold content
- Use `dynamic()` imports for heavy components
- Minimize client-side JavaScript where possible
- Prefer Server Components over Client Components

## Mobile Responsiveness
- Mobile-first CSS approach
- Test breakpoints: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px)
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px
- Base font size 16px minimum on mobile
- Use responsive Tailwind classes: `text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg`

## Component Patterns
```tsx
// Use PixelCard for cards
<PixelCard rarity="uncommon">
  <PixelCardHeader>
    <PixelCardTitle>Title</PixelCardTitle>
  </PixelCardHeader>
  <PixelCardContent>Content</PixelCardContent>
</PixelCard>

// Use PixelButton for buttons
<PixelButton variant="default" size="lg">
  Get Started
</PixelButton>
```

## File Organization
- Pages: `src/app/`
- Marketing pages: `src/app/(marketing)/`
- Components: `src/components/`
- Marketing components: `src/components/marketing/`
- UI primitives: `src/components/ui/`

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Convex (backend)
- Clerk (auth)
- Framer Motion (animations)
- lucide-react (icons)
